    • Method Detail

      • getTreeLock

        public ReentrantReadWriteLock getTreeLock()
        Description copied from interface: ITreeContext
        Returns a Lock object that can be used to lock the entire object tree this object is in. Using this lock, operations such as transferring objects to another parent, removing objects, etc. can be performed in a thread safe manner.

        Note: this method only returns the Lock itself! This method does not perform any locking whatsoever. The actual locking will have to be performed by the caller on the returned lock object.

        Specified by:
        getTreeLock in interface ITreeContext
        Returns:
        the ReentrantReadWriteLock used internally

      • getSafeWriteLock

        public Lock getSafeWriteLock()
        Description copied from interface: ITreeContext
        Obtains a write lock for the tree. By attaching the object to another root object with another tree lock while waiting for the lock, the lock object might change. After obtaining the lock, this method checks that this did not happen and the correct lock was obtained.
        Specified by:
        getSafeWriteLock in interface ITreeContext
        Returns:
        the lock that was acquired
